{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, Centaurian architectures could fuse human insight with AI algorithms in a shared decision-making environment.",
    "Information travels vertically through these spaces-from raw input at the surface to internal processing and back.",
    "There may also be horizontal flows where agents collaborate within a given space.",
    "Feedback loops enable adaptive behavior, such as refining protocols or redistributing tasks in real time based on performance.",
    "Each of these spaces can be seen as managed by an associated group-agent, facilitating distributed problem-solving among a group of users within a networked system or application."
  ]
}